WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:13.305 --> 00:00:16.767
[loud indistinct chatter]

3
00:00:16.850 --> 00:00:18.101
[bell dinging]

4
00:00:18.185 --> 00:00:22.064
- All right. everybody.
settle down!

5
00:00:22.147 --> 00:00:23.315
Good.

6
00:00:23.398 --> 00:00:25.442
Now. Robby has something
important to say.

7
00:00:25.526 --> 00:00:26.902
- I know that this isn't easy.

8
00:00:26.985 --> 00:00:29.029
We're going to help you
address any challenges

9
00:00:29.112 --> 00:00:30.405
that you might be having.

10
00:00:30.489 --> 00:00:32.281
If you have any concerns.
just raise your hand.

11
00:00:32.323 --> 00:00:35.035
- Emma. write all this down.
- Dr. Mohan.

12
00:00:35.118 --> 00:00:37.287
- Medication orders aren't
coming up from the pharmacy.

13
00:00:37.371 --> 00:00:39.289
- Check with the clinical
pharmacist

14
00:00:39.331 --> 00:00:40.958
to see if it's in the PDS.

15
00:00:41.041 --> 00:00:42.543
If it's not.
then give the third copy

16
00:00:42.626 --> 00:00:44.336
of the order sheet
to Dr. Nordt.

17
00:00:44.419 --> 00:00:46.129
- We're gonna need more people
to run it down.

18
00:00:46.171 --> 00:00:47.464
- We'll work on it.
Langdon.

19
00:00:47.506 --> 00:00:49.007
- I can't find
the patient clipboards.

20
00:00:49.091 --> 00:00:51.260
- Clipboards need to stay here
for orders and labs.

21
00:00:51.343 --> 00:00:53.095
- Wait. so how do
we write our notes?

22
00:00:53.136 --> 00:00:55.639
- Take the T sheet to the
bedside. not the whole chart.

23
00:00:55.722 --> 00:00:57.474
Same goes for nursing notes.

24
00:00:57.558 --> 00:00:59.309
- Princess.
- Fax machine is down.

25
00:00:59.351 --> 00:01:01.645
Error message E6.
- What the hell does that mean?

26
00:01:01.728 --> 00:01:03.939
- You can check the manual.
- There isn't one.

27
00:01:04.022 --> 00:01:05.232
- Okay. Perlah.

28
00:01:05.315 --> 00:01:06.817
why don't you take your phone
out to the base?

29
00:01:06.900 --> 00:01:08.986
See if you can get service.
find a manual online.

30
00:01:09.027 --> 00:01:11.738
[both speaking Tagalog]

31
00:01:11.822 --> 00:01:12.990
- What else?

32
00:01:13.031 --> 00:01:14.533
Ogilvie. put your hand down.
Santos.

33
00:01:14.616 --> 00:01:16.201
- We've gotten
a few CT results back

34
00:01:16.285 --> 00:01:17.536
but nothing on plain films.

35
00:01:17.619 --> 00:01:19.329
- That's probably
because they're all sitting

36
00:01:19.371 --> 00:01:21.498
on the portable machine
not getting to radiology.

37
00:01:21.539 --> 00:01:23.166
I'll take care of this.
- You be patient.

38
00:01:23.208 --> 00:01:26.128
Help each other. Thank you.
- [scoffs]

39
00:01:26.211 --> 00:01:28.170
- We need to call in
extra help.

40
00:01:28.213 --> 00:01:30.507
- At 3:00 p.m. on a holiday?
- I know people. buddy.

41
00:01:30.549 --> 00:01:33.634
- I have a 32-year-old woman
with severe abdominal pain.

42
00:01:33.719 --> 00:01:35.345
Do we have a bed?
- Not at the moment.

43
00:01:35.387 --> 00:01:36.638
- I'll take her.
- Incoming.

44
00:01:36.722 --> 00:01:37.681
- Thank you.

45
00:01:37.723 --> 00:01:39.473
Santos. Javadi. you're up.

46
00:01:39.558 --> 00:01:41.977
- Trauma one's open.

47
00:01:42.060 --> 00:01:43.478
- 12-year-old Jude Augustin--

48
00:01:43.520 --> 00:01:45.689
firecracker exploded.
nondominant left hand.

49
00:01:45.771 --> 00:01:47.691
Good vitals.
25 of fent so far.

50
00:01:47.733 --> 00:01:49.026
- Any other injuries?

51
00:01:49.067 --> 00:01:50.860
- No. but seems to have
lost two of his fingers.

52
00:01:50.902 --> 00:01:52.362
- Did you bring 'em?
- Blown to bits.

53
00:01:52.446 --> 00:01:54.197
- It really hurts.
- I'm sure it does.

54
00:01:54.281 --> 00:01:56.033
We'll do something for that.

55
00:01:56.116 --> 00:01:58.118
Parents?
- Not on scene.

56
00:02:00.329 --> 00:02:01.288
- Ready?

57
00:02:01.371 --> 00:02:03.373
One. two. three.

58
00:02:03.415 --> 00:02:04.833
- Hey. Jude.

59
00:02:04.875 --> 00:02:07.002
do you know your mom
or your dad's telephone number?

60
00:02:07.085 --> 00:02:09.378
- No.
But I know my sister's.

61
00:02:09.463 --> 00:02:11.131
- Okay.

62
00:02:11.214 --> 00:02:13.550
- Good breath sounds.
- Abdomen nontender.

63
00:02:13.634 --> 00:02:14.968
- Heart rate 112.

64
00:02:15.052 --> 00:02:16.678
- Put this around
his left forearm.

65
00:02:16.762 --> 00:02:18.388
- Is that good?
- That is very good.

66
00:02:18.472 --> 00:02:20.891
I want to do another 25 of fent
before we open this bandage.

67
00:02:20.932 --> 00:02:22.601
- Can you tell us
what happened?

68
00:02:22.684 --> 00:02:25.520
- My friends had firecrackers.
- 25 fent on board.

69
00:02:25.603 --> 00:02:28.231
- I lit one.
and it went off fast.

70
00:02:28.273 --> 00:02:30.233
I-I dropped it. but...

71
00:02:30.275 --> 00:02:32.069
- We're gonna take
your bandage off now. okay?

72
00:02:32.152 --> 00:02:34.029
- I don't want to see.
- You don't have to.

73
00:02:34.112 --> 00:02:35.822
Just look at me.

74
00:02:35.906 --> 00:02:37.199
- Okay.

75
00:02:37.281 --> 00:02:40.035
Cutting.

76
00:02:40.118 --> 00:02:42.079
[Jude breathing rapidly]
Sorry.

77
00:02:42.162 --> 00:02:43.829
You're doing great.

78
00:02:43.914 --> 00:02:46.583
[monitor beeping]

79
00:02:46.625 --> 00:02:49.252
That looks like a lot more
than a firecracker.

80
00:02:49.336 --> 00:02:51.755
- More like an M-80
or a cherry bomb.

81
00:02:51.838 --> 00:02:53.715
- It's really good
that you dropped it.

82
00:02:53.799 --> 00:02:55.550
You saved the rest
of your hand.

83
00:02:55.634 --> 00:02:57.094
- Digits 4 and 5 avulsed.

84
00:02:57.177 --> 00:02:59.596
Distal metacarpals 4 and 5
also gone with exposed bone.

85
00:02:59.680 --> 00:03:01.264
Soft-tissue damage
on the palmar aspect.

86
00:03:01.348 --> 00:03:03.850
less so on dorsal--
some burns on wound edges.

87
00:03:03.934 --> 00:03:08.105
- Jude. can you bend your
fingers for me up and down?

88
00:03:08.146 --> 00:03:10.023
- Really good job.
Really good job.

89
00:03:10.107 --> 00:03:12.442
- How bad is it?
- You lost two fingers.

90
00:03:12.484 --> 00:03:15.112
But it seems like the rest
are gonna be okay.

91
00:03:15.195 --> 00:03:17.406
- Oh. no.
I fucked up!

92
00:03:17.489 --> 00:03:19.950
- All right. can we do
a wrist block for the pain?

93
00:03:19.991 --> 00:03:22.786
- I want to do a very detailed
motor and sensory exam first.

94
00:03:22.869 --> 00:03:25.454
- We're gonna continue
our exam now. okay. Jude?

95
00:03:25.539 --> 00:03:28.750
[beeping continues]

96
00:03:28.834 --> 00:03:30.085
- Okay. thanks.

97
00:03:30.168 --> 00:03:32.421
ICU can take her
after the next neuro exam.

98
00:03:32.504 --> 00:03:33.797
- The ICU?

99
00:03:33.880 --> 00:03:36.049
- It's just so she
can be monitored for the rest

100
00:03:36.133 --> 00:03:37.968
of the day.

101
00:03:38.009 --> 00:03:40.971
4 millimeters and reactive.

102
00:03:41.054 --> 00:03:42.264
Mel.

103
00:03:42.305 --> 00:03:44.933
4 millimeters and reactive.
- Yep. got it.

104
00:03:45.016 --> 00:03:47.686
- I could sort of make out
your hand.

105
00:03:50.897 --> 00:03:52.983
- Can you cover your good eye?

106
00:03:53.024 --> 00:03:56.486
How many fingers
am I holding up?

107
00:03:56.528 --> 00:03:57.654
- Three.

108
00:03:59.531 --> 00:04:00.866
- That's good news.

109
00:04:00.949 --> 00:04:04.035
- So the medicine worked?
She's out of the woods?

110
00:04:04.119 --> 00:04:05.454
- Um. possibly.

111
00:04:05.495 --> 00:04:06.580
It's...

112
00:04:06.663 --> 00:04:09.791
Okay. um. cover your eye again.

113
00:04:09.833 --> 00:04:12.669
All right. what do you see?

114
00:04:12.753 --> 00:04:16.630
- Top line is E.
- All right. and the next one?

115
00:04:18.925 --> 00:04:20.844
- Nothing.

116
00:04:20.927 --> 00:04:24.139
- Okay. well. that's 20/200.

117
00:04:24.222 --> 00:04:25.348
- Meaning?

118
00:04:25.432 --> 00:04:27.517
- Uh. what a healthy eye
can see at 200 feet.

119
00:04:27.559 --> 00:04:28.810
she can see at 20 feet.

120
00:04:28.894 --> 00:04:31.688
- Is that good?
- Yeah. It's much better.

121
00:04:31.772 --> 00:04:34.816
Um. and it can continue
to improve over time.

122
00:04:34.900 --> 00:04:37.527
[pen scratching]
- Thank you. Dr. King.

123
00:04:37.611 --> 00:04:40.197
- Um. I'm gonna take
a quick break

124
00:04:40.238 --> 00:04:41.948
before my deposition.
- Mm-hmm.

125
00:04:42.032 --> 00:04:44.201
- So I'll let Robby know
that I'm off the clock

126
00:04:44.242 --> 00:04:46.328
for the time being.
- Good luck.

127
00:04:46.411 --> 00:04:47.746
- Thanks.

128
00:04:49.956 --> 00:04:51.625
- Mel.
- Hey.

129
00:04:51.707 --> 00:04:53.043
- You have a visitor in chairs.

130
00:04:53.084 --> 00:04:56.254
- What? Who?
- Said she's your sister.

131
00:04:56.338 --> 00:04:57.714
- Becca?

132
00:05:00.634 --> 00:05:01.676
[device beeps]

133
00:05:01.760 --> 00:05:03.553
- Yep.
You have heat exhaustion.

134
00:05:03.595 --> 00:05:05.555
- It usually gets better
with Aleve.

135
00:05:05.639 --> 00:05:07.390
but today was really bad.

136
00:05:07.432 --> 00:05:09.643
- Same pain you had before?
- Mm-hmm.

137
00:05:09.726 --> 00:05:11.728
- From a cyst?
- I think so.

138
00:05:11.770 --> 00:05:14.022
I have PCOS.

139
00:05:14.105 --> 00:05:16.691
- Is the. uh--is the pain
always on your left?

140
00:05:16.775 --> 00:05:17.984
- Today it is.

141
00:05:18.068 --> 00:05:20.862
- We will check a UA
and urine pregnancy test.

142
00:05:20.946 --> 00:05:22.405
and I'll give you
a shot of Toradol.

143
00:05:22.489 --> 00:05:25.075
It's something a little
stronger for the pain.

144
00:05:25.158 --> 00:05:26.785
- I'm not pregnant. I promise.

145
00:05:26.868 --> 00:05:30.080
- No. we have to.
It's hospital policy.

146
00:05:30.121 --> 00:05:33.707
- You guys still write stuff
down on paper?

147
00:05:33.792 --> 00:05:36.378
- Today we do. yeah.

148
00:05:36.461 --> 00:05:39.631
[indistinct chatter]

149
00:05:43.343 --> 00:05:44.553
- Are you a doctor?

150
00:05:44.636 --> 00:05:46.888
I've been waiting hours
to be seen.

151
00:05:46.930 --> 00:05:48.223
- Quick question--
- Oh.

152
00:05:48.265 --> 00:05:51.433
- Hey. watch the walker.
- This thing is useless.

153
00:05:51.476 --> 00:05:53.895
- Sorry. I just. um. um--
we're really busy.

154
00:05:53.979 --> 00:05:55.939
And someone
will see you in a second.

155
00:05:56.022 --> 00:05:58.316
[chatter continues]

156
00:05:58.400 --> 00:06:01.278
Becca.
- Mel. hi.

157
00:06:01.361 --> 00:06:04.155
- Is everything okay?
- Yeah. I have a stomachache.

158
00:06:04.239 --> 00:06:06.116
- Did you see
the residential-care nurse?

159
00:06:06.199 --> 00:06:07.409
- She was out for the Fourth.

160
00:06:07.492 --> 00:06:09.077
but I talked to her
on the phone.

161
00:06:09.160 --> 00:06:11.121
She told me to come here.
and Geri brought me.

162
00:06:11.162 --> 00:06:12.539
- Thank you.
- No problem.

163
00:06:12.622 --> 00:06:14.708
I'll wait for you.
- Okay.

164
00:06:14.791 --> 00:06:16.543
- Okay.
Come on. this way.

165
00:06:16.626 --> 00:06:18.378
Uh. just through here.

166
00:06:18.461 --> 00:06:22.132
- Is it always like this?
- Yeah. pretty much.

167
00:06:22.173 --> 00:06:25.468
- Wow. There are a lot
of smelly people.

168
00:06:25.552 --> 00:06:26.803
- Yeah.

169
00:06:26.887 --> 00:06:28.471
- Are you going
to help them all?

170
00:06:28.513 --> 00:06:30.640
- Yeah. but. um. let's start
with you first.

171
00:06:30.682 --> 00:06:32.183
- Okay.

172
00:06:32.267 --> 00:06:35.478
- How's the pain?
- I can't feel my hand anymore.

173
00:06:35.520 --> 00:06:36.980
- Ancef's on board.

174
00:06:37.063 --> 00:06:39.316
- Okay. we're going to clean
out your hand with saline--

175
00:06:39.399 --> 00:06:41.860
salt water.
- Okay.

176
00:06:45.655 --> 00:06:47.282
- What's up?

177
00:06:47.365 --> 00:06:48.658
- Hand versus M-80.

178
00:06:48.742 --> 00:06:50.827
- Hmm. Surprised we've only
seen one of these.

179
00:06:50.911 --> 00:06:52.329
- The day's still young yet.

180
00:06:52.370 --> 00:06:54.664
Lost fourth metacarpal.
mid-shaft on the fifth.

181
00:06:54.748 --> 00:06:56.917
- Bummer.

182
00:06:57.000 --> 00:06:59.169
Hello. I'm Dr. Garcia
from surgery.

183
00:06:59.252 --> 00:07:00.837
- I'm gonna have surgery?
- Yes.

184
00:07:00.921 --> 00:07:03.506
The first operation is to clean
everything up

185
00:07:03.590 --> 00:07:06.009
and cover where the skin
is missing.

186
00:07:06.092 --> 00:07:07.969
- But you still have your thumb

187
00:07:08.053 --> 00:07:10.639
and your most important
fingers.

188
00:07:13.350 --> 00:07:16.019
- What'd you give him for pain?
- We did regional blocks.

189
00:07:16.102 --> 00:07:18.813
- Hand surgery always wants to
document their own neuro exam.

190
00:07:18.855 --> 00:07:21.107
- Sensation is intact
to light touch and pinprick

191
00:07:21.191 --> 00:07:23.193
throughout the digits
in the remaining hand.

192
00:07:23.276 --> 00:07:25.445
- [exhales deeply]

193
00:07:25.528 --> 00:07:28.365
- Um. yeah. FDS and FTPs
and extensor function

194
00:07:28.448 --> 00:07:29.824
was all intact.

195
00:07:29.908 --> 00:07:31.868
- Need parental consent
for surgery.

196
00:07:31.910 --> 00:07:34.287
- Yeah. we're working on that.
- Dr. Robby?

197
00:07:37.957 --> 00:07:41.211
- I smell alcohol
on his breath.

198
00:07:41.294 --> 00:07:42.420
- He's in line for the OR.

199
00:07:42.504 --> 00:07:44.005
Might be a little bit
of a wait.

200
00:07:44.089 --> 00:07:45.715
Ortho's still in
with Allen Billings--

201
00:07:45.799 --> 00:07:47.842
that open shoulder dislocation
that came back from Westbridge.

202
00:07:47.926 --> 00:07:49.219
- He's still in surgery?

203
00:07:49.302 --> 00:07:51.054
- He waited an hour
to be cleared by anesthesia.

204
00:07:51.096 --> 00:07:52.347
- Is the insurance company

205
00:07:52.430 --> 00:07:54.015
gonna cover the cost
of the surgery?

206
00:07:54.099 --> 00:07:55.558
- Yeah. since Westbridge
is still down.

207
00:07:55.600 --> 00:07:57.227
- Well. good.
because the delay in care

208
00:07:57.310 --> 00:07:58.979
definitely increased the chance
of a post-op infection.

209
00:07:59.062 --> 00:08:00.855
- You got to love it
when insurance companies

210
00:08:00.939 --> 00:08:02.232
make medical decisions.

211
00:08:02.315 --> 00:08:03.608
- Hey.
- What's up?

212
00:08:03.692 --> 00:08:05.402
- Do you still need
a rain check

213
00:08:05.443 --> 00:08:06.778
for watching fireworks tonight?

214
00:08:06.861 --> 00:08:08.279
I thought you were coming over.

215
00:08:08.363 --> 00:08:11.032
- I made other plans.

216
00:08:11.116 --> 00:08:12.534
- Okay. cool.

217
00:08:12.617 --> 00:08:14.577
I'll try hitting you up
tomorrow.

218
00:08:14.661 --> 00:08:16.705
- We're just keeping
it casual. right?

219
00:08:16.788 --> 00:08:18.123
- For sure.

220
00:08:21.459 --> 00:08:23.044
[indistinct chatter]
- Yeah.

221
00:08:23.128 --> 00:08:25.005
Thank you.
Yeah. bye.

222
00:08:25.088 --> 00:08:26.423
Oh. uh. hey.

223
00:08:26.506 --> 00:08:28.508
I just got a hold of the sister
of the heavy patient

224
00:08:28.591 --> 00:08:30.010
Abbot's taking to Presby.

225
00:08:30.093 --> 00:08:32.261
She still lives in Arizona.
but she is willing to talk

226
00:08:32.345 --> 00:08:33.763
to him when he's back.

227
00:08:33.804 --> 00:08:34.931
- That's good news.

228
00:08:35.015 --> 00:08:36.933
- When do you think
that might be?

229
00:08:36.975 --> 00:08:39.227
- Depends on how crazy
it is over at Presby.

230
00:08:39.309 --> 00:08:41.062
If it's anything
like here. who knows?

231
00:08:41.145 --> 00:08:42.438
- Yeah.
[bell dings]

232
00:08:42.480 --> 00:08:44.107
- Um. is help on the way?

233
00:08:44.149 --> 00:08:45.483
- Ah. ye of little faith.

234
00:08:45.567 --> 00:08:48.069
You got a gumband?

235
00:08:48.153 --> 00:08:51.281
- Thanks.
Keep losing these.

236
00:08:51.364 --> 00:08:53.116
Oh. this fucking day.

237
00:08:53.199 --> 00:08:55.618
- Thought I was gonna get
a clean getaway for my trip.

238
00:08:55.702 --> 00:08:57.454
- God gives
His toughest battles

239
00:08:57.537 --> 00:08:58.955
to His strongest soldiers.

240
00:08:58.997 --> 00:09:01.166
- Dana. is there a room open?
This is my sister.

241
00:09:01.249 --> 00:09:03.418
She's in a lot of pain.
and--and we need a bed ASAP.

242
00:09:03.501 --> 00:09:04.961
- My name is Becca.
not "my sister."

243
00:09:05.045 --> 00:09:06.296
- Sorry. right.

244
00:09:06.379 --> 00:09:08.715
Um. Dana. Dr. Robby.
this is my--

245
00:09:08.798 --> 00:09:09.966
my--Becca.

246
00:09:10.050 --> 00:09:11.217
- Nice to meet you.

247
00:09:11.301 --> 00:09:14.262
- You're Dr. Robby?
Cool.

248
00:09:14.304 --> 00:09:16.931
- Central 7 was just cleaned.
Anything I can get you. hon?

249
00:09:17.015 --> 00:09:18.600
- No. thank you.

250
00:09:21.186 --> 00:09:23.605
- Oh. wait. Becca.
Come here.

251
00:09:23.688 --> 00:09:28.151
Come this way.
We're going right in here.

252
00:09:28.234 --> 00:09:31.237
All right. so. um. you're gonna
need to get undressed

253
00:09:31.321 --> 00:09:33.823
and get into the gown.
which should be on the bed.

254
00:09:33.907 --> 00:09:36.534
Then we're gonna do an
evaluation and take a history.

255
00:09:36.618 --> 00:09:38.036
That's a lot of questions.

256
00:09:38.119 --> 00:09:40.121
like. like. a lot. a lot
of questions. which we'll do.

257
00:09:40.205 --> 00:09:41.831
And then a physical exam.
of course.

258
00:09:41.915 --> 00:09:44.167
- Mel. I've been
to the doctor's before.

259
00:09:44.250 --> 00:09:46.377
[chuckles]
- Right. Sorry.

260
00:09:46.461 --> 00:09:49.547
I just--I-I really want this
to be done the right way.

261
00:09:49.631 --> 00:09:53.843
[cell phone ringing]

262
00:09:53.885 --> 00:09:55.553
- Do you need to take
that call?

263
00:09:55.637 --> 00:09:58.014
- Uh. no. it's. um--
it's a reminder alarm

264
00:09:58.098 --> 00:10:00.558
for this important meeting
I have in 15 minutes.

265
00:10:00.642 --> 00:10:02.811
- Um. do you have to go?

266
00:10:02.852 --> 00:10:04.938
- Let's just get you
taken care of first. all right?

267
00:10:05.021 --> 00:10:07.816
So just change into the gown.
I'll be behind the curtain.

268
00:10:07.857 --> 00:10:10.276
- Okay.

269
00:10:10.360 --> 00:10:12.237
- Okay.

270
00:10:20.078 --> 00:10:21.830
- [clears throat]

271
00:10:21.913 --> 00:10:25.041
Your grand prize.

272
00:10:25.083 --> 00:10:28.294
- All I see is green. baby.

273
00:10:28.378 --> 00:10:30.463
[laughs]

274
00:10:36.302 --> 00:10:38.847
- Oh.
What's up with her?

275
00:10:38.930 --> 00:10:41.558
- Fax machine has paper jam--
so annoying.

276
00:10:41.599 --> 00:10:43.059
- Hmm.

277
00:10:49.607 --> 00:10:51.860
- You want me to try?
- No.

278
00:10:51.943 --> 00:10:54.237
- Oh. huzzah.
- I got it.

279
00:10:54.320 --> 00:10:56.739
[fax machine whirring]

280
00:10:56.823 --> 00:10:58.533
[beeps]

281
00:10:58.616 --> 00:11:00.201
What's it say?
- "Replace toner."

282
00:11:00.285 --> 00:11:01.536
We live in hell.

283
00:11:01.619 --> 00:11:03.288
- Oh. where can we get that?
- 1988.

284
00:11:03.371 --> 00:11:05.790
You ever seen one of these?
- Honestly. no.

285
00:11:05.874 --> 00:11:07.750
- How are we gonna get labs
and X-rays to the wards?

286
00:11:07.834 --> 00:11:09.544
- The old-fashioned way.
runners.

287
00:11:09.627 --> 00:11:11.880
- [sighs] I'll check if they
can spare a couple clerks

288
00:11:11.963 --> 00:11:13.506
from upstairs.

289
00:11:17.468 --> 00:11:18.595
- When were you first diagnosed

290
00:11:18.636 --> 00:11:20.388
with polycystic ovarian
syndrome?

291
00:11:20.471 --> 00:11:21.723
- Last summer.

292
00:11:21.806 --> 00:11:23.558
- That's when
the symptoms started?

293
00:11:23.641 --> 00:11:26.269
- No. I've had years of pain.
hormonal changes.

294
00:11:26.311 --> 00:11:27.729
and an abnormal period.

295
00:11:27.770 --> 00:11:30.064
I was finally diagnosed
after switching to a gyno

296
00:11:30.148 --> 00:11:31.774
who actually listened to me.

297
00:11:31.858 --> 00:11:35.278
- Yeah. it can take time
to make the diagnosis.

298
00:11:35.320 --> 00:11:38.573
- That sounds like an excuse
for lazy doctoring.

299
00:11:38.656 --> 00:11:41.576
And it doesn't help that some
of you don't listen to women.

300
00:11:41.659 --> 00:11:43.286
let alone brown ones.

301
00:11:43.369 --> 00:11:44.829
It hasn't been easy.

302
00:11:44.913 --> 00:11:46.998
- How's your pain now?
- Better.

303
00:11:47.081 --> 00:11:49.417
- What was she given?
- IM Toradol.

304
00:11:49.459 --> 00:11:52.587
Have you had a transvaginal
ultrasound before?

305
00:11:52.670 --> 00:11:54.422
- I've lost count
of how many times.

306
00:11:54.464 --> 00:11:56.633
- Okay. if you want
to scoot your bottom down.

307
00:11:56.716 --> 00:11:59.636
I'll help you put your feet
in the leg rests here.

308
00:11:59.677 --> 00:12:02.096
Yep. you got it.

309
00:12:02.180 --> 00:12:04.015
- [clears throat]

310
00:12:04.098 --> 00:12:06.935
[chair rolls]

311
00:12:07.018 --> 00:12:09.103
[bed clanks]

312
00:12:10.521 --> 00:12:12.440
- Okay. ready to go here?

313
00:12:12.523 --> 00:12:15.360
Cold gel and some pressure.

314
00:12:18.196 --> 00:12:20.490
Okay.

315
00:12:20.531 --> 00:12:22.492
Okay. ectopic is unlikely

316
00:12:22.533 --> 00:12:24.827
since the urine pregnancy
was negative.

317
00:12:24.869 --> 00:12:26.829
- I'm hoping
it'll be positive one day.

318
00:12:26.913 --> 00:12:29.666
- Oh. are you trying?
- Not at the moment.

319
00:12:29.749 --> 00:12:31.834
I'm getting married
in September.

320
00:12:31.918 --> 00:12:35.129
- Oh. congratulations.
- Okay.

321
00:12:35.213 --> 00:12:38.174
A bunch of small cysts--
to be expected.

322
00:12:38.216 --> 00:12:41.552
But then there's one big one.
about 5 centimeters.

323
00:12:41.636 --> 00:12:43.846
- My gyno's
been monitoring her.

324
00:12:43.930 --> 00:12:45.139
- Mm-hmm.

325
00:12:45.223 --> 00:12:46.557
With a little bit
of free fluid.

326
00:12:46.641 --> 00:12:49.185
Checking blood flow
to the ovary.

327
00:12:49.269 --> 00:12:51.646
Red is for artery.
Blue is for vein.

328
00:12:51.729 --> 00:12:53.356
Okay. looks good.

329
00:12:53.439 --> 00:12:55.984
Coming out now.

330
00:12:56.067 --> 00:12:57.986
- Sorry.
- Okay.

331
00:12:59.237 --> 00:13:02.991
We will be back when we get
your blood-test results.

332
00:13:05.410 --> 00:13:06.703
All right. what do you think?

333
00:13:06.786 --> 00:13:08.705
- She probably had
a small fluid leak

334
00:13:08.746 --> 00:13:10.540
from the cyst
that caused the pain

335
00:13:10.581 --> 00:13:12.458
that improved
with a nonsteroidal.

336
00:13:12.542 --> 00:13:15.712
- And what's your plan?
- Discharge with naproxen?

337
00:13:15.753 --> 00:13:18.798
- Do you think that just might
be what her doctors in the past

338
00:13:18.881 --> 00:13:20.049
have done?

339
00:13:20.091 --> 00:13:21.718
- Well. she said
she's feeling better.

340
00:13:21.801 --> 00:13:23.011
We can free up a bed.

341
00:13:23.094 --> 00:13:24.637
- Mm. she didn't look good
in triage.

342
00:13:24.721 --> 00:13:27.056
and her pain was way more
severe than previous episodes.

343
00:13:27.098 --> 00:13:29.058
I think we observe her
for a bit.

344
00:13:29.100 --> 00:13:30.643
- Okay.

345
00:13:30.727 --> 00:13:34.480
- Mr. Green. this is Dr. Mohan
and student doctor Ogilvie.

346
00:13:34.564 --> 00:13:36.649
- Uh. what can you tell me
about your flank pain?

347
00:13:36.733 --> 00:13:38.818
- Feels like
another kidney stone.

348
00:13:38.901 --> 00:13:40.320
- You've had them before?

349
00:13:40.403 --> 00:13:42.405
- I said "another." which means
an additional thing

350
00:13:42.488 --> 00:13:44.615
of the same type.

351
00:13:44.699 --> 00:13:47.035
I teach English at Point Park.

352
00:13:47.118 --> 00:13:48.286
- Triggering.

353
00:13:48.369 --> 00:13:50.747
My dad's a high-school
English teacher.

354
00:13:50.788 --> 00:13:52.123
- Oh.

355
00:13:52.206 --> 00:13:55.626
Well. you went into medicine.
He must be really proud.

356
00:13:55.710 --> 00:13:57.420
- You'd have to ask him.

357
00:13:57.462 --> 00:13:59.088
- Getting back to your pain.

358
00:13:59.130 --> 00:14:01.466
it feels like something
you've experienced before?

359
00:14:01.549 --> 00:14:03.426
- Same as always. left kidney.

360
00:14:03.509 --> 00:14:05.428
Started about 10:00 p.m.
last night.

361
00:14:05.511 --> 00:14:07.597
- Any fever.
blood in the urine?

362
00:14:07.680 --> 00:14:08.931
- No.
Uh. no fever.

363
00:14:09.015 --> 00:14:10.975
Urine's a bit darker
than normal.

364
00:14:11.059 --> 00:14:12.977
- Dehydration can lead
to stone formation.

365
00:14:13.061 --> 00:14:14.604
- Lean forward a bit. please.

366
00:14:14.645 --> 00:14:16.939
Check for CVA tenderness.
- Yeah.

367
00:14:16.981 --> 00:14:18.733
All right.

368
00:14:18.816 --> 00:14:20.902
Let me know if there's
any discomfort.

369
00:14:20.985 --> 00:14:23.738
- Mm-hmm.

370
00:14:23.821 --> 00:14:24.739
Ah!
- Sorry.

371
00:14:24.822 --> 00:14:25.865
- Yeah.

372
00:14:25.948 --> 00:14:27.742
- We'll order medication
and a few tests.

373
00:14:27.825 --> 00:14:28.910
- Okay.

374
00:14:31.704 --> 00:14:33.748
- Um. dip urine. Chem Seven.

375
00:14:33.831 --> 00:14:35.750
bedside ultrasound
to check for hydro.

376
00:14:35.833 --> 00:14:37.794
and ketorolac for pain.
- Sounds good.

377
00:14:37.877 --> 00:14:39.337
- Okay.

378
00:14:44.050 --> 00:14:45.635
- Really putting me to work.

379
00:14:45.676 --> 00:14:47.678
- It's been a very busy day.
Dr. Barker.

380
00:14:47.762 --> 00:14:49.514
- Call me Nick.

381
00:14:51.015 --> 00:14:53.684
- What's all this?
- I brought radiology to us.

382
00:14:53.768 --> 00:14:56.437
Dr. Barker. Nick. will have
wet-read results for us

383
00:14:56.479 --> 00:14:57.814
in no time.
- Good idea.

384
00:14:57.855 --> 00:15:00.024
- Thank you.
- "Wet read"?

385
00:15:00.108 --> 00:15:01.692
- You ever take
a photography class?

386
00:15:01.776 --> 00:15:03.152
- Yeah. in. like.
middle school.

387
00:15:03.236 --> 00:15:04.987
- So. before digital
technology. X-ray films

388
00:15:05.029 --> 00:15:07.698
were physically developed
in a darkroom. in baths.

389
00:15:07.782 --> 00:15:09.534
thus wet read.

390
00:15:09.617 --> 00:15:10.660
- Oh. cool.

391
00:15:10.743 --> 00:15:13.371
- He's taking up
a lot of space.

392
00:15:13.454 --> 00:15:15.957
Got an update from Dylan
on our abandoned baby.

393
00:15:16.040 --> 00:15:18.793
CYF has requested an emergency
custody authorization.

394
00:15:18.876 --> 00:15:21.504
Once we get a court order. we
can place her in foster care.

395
00:15:21.587 --> 00:15:24.006
- I love photography.
- [chuckles]

396
00:15:24.090 --> 00:15:25.341
- Jesus Christ.
- Dr. Robby?

397
00:15:25.425 --> 00:15:26.968
Dr. Robby. can I borrow
you for a second?

398
00:15:27.051 --> 00:15:28.344
- Sure.
What can I do for you?

399
00:15:28.386 --> 00:15:29.971
- Well. she said she
has a stomachache.

400
00:15:30.054 --> 00:15:31.973
but belly pain can mean a lot
of different things--

401
00:15:32.014 --> 00:15:34.809
- Okay. okay. okay. breathe.
- I'm looking for Dr. Mel King.

402
00:15:34.892 --> 00:15:36.686
- Yes?

403
00:15:36.727 --> 00:15:38.980
- I'm Morgan Stiles. one
of the hospital's attorneys.

404
00:15:39.063 --> 00:15:41.774
I'm here to escort you upstairs
for your deposition.

405
00:15:41.858 --> 00:15:43.317
- Right now?

406
00:15:43.359 --> 00:15:47.196
- Morgan. can I borrow Dr. King
for just a moment?

407
00:15:47.238 --> 00:15:48.573
- Sure.

408
00:15:50.241 --> 00:15:51.534
- It's gonna be fine.

409
00:15:51.576 --> 00:15:53.536
- I can't go up now
because of Becca.

410
00:15:53.619 --> 00:15:55.580
- You probably shouldn't be
caring for Becca.

411
00:15:55.663 --> 00:15:57.665
It's not a good idea
to care for family members.

412
00:15:57.748 --> 00:15:59.040
It's hard to stay objective.

413
00:15:59.125 --> 00:16:00.543
Let's see who's available.

414
00:16:00.626 --> 00:16:01.878
Hey. are you free?

415
00:16:01.961 --> 00:16:04.589
- Is anybody really free?

416
00:16:04.672 --> 00:16:06.215
- Not an R2.

417
00:16:06.299 --> 00:16:08.718
- Ah. just the guy
we were looking for.

418
00:16:08.759 --> 00:16:10.094
- Need something?
- Yes.

419
00:16:10.178 --> 00:16:12.054
Uh-huh. mm-hmm.
- Sure.

420
00:16:12.138 --> 00:16:13.931
Dr. King's sister
has a bellyache.

421
00:16:14.015 --> 00:16:15.224
The case is now yours.
- Sure.

422
00:16:15.266 --> 00:16:17.059
- You can pick up
the rest of her patients

423
00:16:17.143 --> 00:16:18.728
while she's doing
her deposition.

424
00:16:18.811 --> 00:16:20.480
- How am I supposed to catch up
on my outstanding charts

425
00:16:20.563 --> 00:16:22.565
with extra patients
and the computer system down?

426
00:16:22.648 --> 00:16:24.400
- The same way
that the rest of us do.

427
00:16:24.484 --> 00:16:26.903
You can finish your charting
when you finish your shift.

428
00:16:26.986 --> 00:16:29.113
- Fucking fantastic.

429
00:16:33.451 --> 00:16:35.077
- Hi. Becca.
- Hi.

430
00:16:35.119 --> 00:16:36.913
- Um. This is Dr. Langdon.
[door closes]

431
00:16:36.996 --> 00:16:38.831
He'll be taking care of you.

432
00:16:38.915 --> 00:16:41.375
- You have really nice hair.
Dr. Langdon.

433
00:16:41.459 --> 00:16:43.169
- [chuckles]
Thank you.

434
00:16:43.252 --> 00:16:46.756
Mel. would you mind turning off
the lights on your way out?

435
00:16:46.839 --> 00:16:48.424
- Of course.

436
00:16:48.508 --> 00:16:51.135
And. um. I'll be back
as soon as I'm done.

437
00:16:51.219 --> 00:16:53.137
And feel free to call me
if anything comes up.

438
00:16:53.221 --> 00:16:55.306
because I can come right--
- Don't--don't worry.

439
00:16:55.389 --> 00:16:58.267
Becca's in good hands.
- I know.

440
00:16:58.309 --> 00:16:59.644
Okay.

441
00:17:07.276 --> 00:17:10.445
- Mel says lots of nice things
about you.

442
00:17:12.406 --> 00:17:13.616
- Okay.

443
00:17:13.657 --> 00:17:15.284
Um...

444
00:17:15.367 --> 00:17:17.619
tell me the reason
you're here today.

445
00:17:17.662 --> 00:17:18.954
- I have a stomachache.

446
00:17:19.038 --> 00:17:20.748
- Your belly hurts?
Where about?

447
00:17:20.830 --> 00:17:23.960
- Right. um--right down here.
- Okay.

448
00:17:24.001 --> 00:17:25.962
Are you experiencing
anything else.

449
00:17:26.045 --> 00:17:27.797
or is it just the stomachache?

450
00:17:27.880 --> 00:17:29.799
- It--it stings when I pee.

451
00:17:29.882 --> 00:17:31.884
- Sometimes when that happens.

452
00:17:31.968 --> 00:17:34.595
women feel like they need
to urinate all the time.

453
00:17:34.679 --> 00:17:36.389
Do you feel that way?
- Yes.

454
00:17:36.472 --> 00:17:38.140
- And what happens when you go?

455
00:17:38.224 --> 00:17:40.893
- Hardly anything comes out.

456
00:17:40.977 --> 00:17:42.436
- That's what I thought.

457
00:17:42.520 --> 00:17:44.939
- Really?
How do you know?

458
00:17:45.022 --> 00:17:46.649
- Well. I've seen
a lot of patients

459
00:17:46.691 --> 00:17:48.985
with the same symptoms.
- So this is normal?

460
00:17:49.068 --> 00:17:50.653
- Yes. it's totally normal.

461
00:17:50.736 --> 00:17:53.155
But we still need to fix it.

462
00:17:53.197 --> 00:17:54.699
- Okay.

463
00:18:00.371 --> 00:18:01.497
- Hey.

464
00:18:01.539 --> 00:18:03.708
How's it going. Roxy?
[door closes]

465
00:18:03.791 --> 00:18:06.002
- A little better.
- Yeah?

466
00:18:06.043 --> 00:18:08.087
- You need more morphine?

467
00:18:13.593 --> 00:18:17.221
- I've been in pain
all this time. my love.

468
00:18:17.305 --> 00:18:19.348
- Why didn't you tell me?

469
00:18:19.432 --> 00:18:22.727
- [sighs] I didn't want
you guys to worry.

470
00:18:24.353 --> 00:18:27.315
I can't pretend anymore.

471
00:18:27.398 --> 00:18:31.027
- Mom. it's so hot outside.
the ice cream's melting.

472
00:18:31.068 --> 00:18:33.863
- [winces. groans]
- We. uh...

473
00:18:33.904 --> 00:18:37.116
we thought we'd indulge a bit.

474
00:18:37.199 --> 00:18:39.035
- Oh. yeah.
- Ooh.

475
00:18:39.118 --> 00:18:40.453
Looks amazing.

476
00:18:40.536 --> 00:18:43.039
- So. uh. which flavor
should we start with?

477
00:18:43.080 --> 00:18:46.167
- Salty caramel.
Mom's favorite.

478
00:18:46.250 --> 00:18:48.753
- You'll need
lots more napkins.

479
00:18:51.088 --> 00:18:52.840
- Mmm.

480
00:18:52.923 --> 00:18:56.052
[indistinct chatter]

481
00:19:02.933 --> 00:19:05.603
- [snaps fingers]
- Rude.

482
00:19:07.688 --> 00:19:09.732
- How's it going in there?
- All good.

483
00:19:09.815 --> 00:19:11.233
Langdon's great with her.

484
00:19:11.275 --> 00:19:13.110
- I got seven more films
ordered. waiting to be shot.

485
00:19:13.194 --> 00:19:15.571
but Dr. Nick here's tying up
the machine.

486
00:19:15.655 --> 00:19:18.282
- Isn't there a USB port
on the front of that portable?

487
00:19:18.366 --> 00:19:21.118
And can't we just download
the films to a workstation

488
00:19:21.202 --> 00:19:22.870
and watch them
without the Internet?

489
00:19:22.953 --> 00:19:24.789
- Yes.
- Oh. right. Forgot about that.

490
00:19:24.872 --> 00:19:27.500
- Is he actually helping.
or is he just distracting?

491
00:19:27.583 --> 00:19:29.418
- Let's download these
and start moving on to folks

492
00:19:29.460 --> 00:19:31.420
waiting for X-rays.
- Great. I'm caught up anyway.

493
00:19:31.504 --> 00:19:33.172
I'll be back
when the next batch is ready.

494
00:19:33.255 --> 00:19:35.341
- Dr. Robby. the guardian
of your missing-fingers kid

495
00:19:35.424 --> 00:19:37.426
in Central 12 has arrived.
- Thank you. Olive.

496
00:19:37.468 --> 00:19:39.553
Will you ask Dr. Santos
to come and meet me. too?

497
00:19:39.637 --> 00:19:41.097
- On it.
- Who's in South 22?

498
00:19:41.138 --> 00:19:42.682
- Nobody.
Headache was discharged.

499
00:19:42.765 --> 00:19:44.433
- Tell that
to the lady on the bed.

500
00:19:44.517 --> 00:19:45.935
- What lady?

501
00:19:45.976 --> 00:19:48.020
- I just tried to put
a hematuria patient in there.

502
00:19:48.104 --> 00:19:50.272
but. uh. it's occupied.
- South 22? You sure?

503
00:19:50.314 --> 00:19:52.066
- I'm positive.
- That's my patient.

504
00:19:52.149 --> 00:19:54.276
- Then why isn't she
on the board?

505
00:19:54.360 --> 00:19:55.695
- I--
She should be.

506
00:19:55.778 --> 00:19:57.446
Olive was bringing her back
from triage.

507
00:19:57.530 --> 00:19:58.906
I picked her right up.

508
00:19:58.989 --> 00:20:00.449
I just assumed
she made it to the board.

509
00:20:00.491 --> 00:20:01.992
- You should've checked.
You should've made sure.

510
00:20:02.076 --> 00:20:03.661
- I-I haven't put anybody
on the board.

511
00:20:03.744 --> 00:20:05.788
I thought the nurses did that.
- We all need to pitch in.

512
00:20:05.871 --> 00:20:07.748
There's no rooms at the moment.
Put hematuria on the wall.

513
00:20:07.832 --> 00:20:10.292
Who's your patient?
- Mrs. Burns. with nausea.

514
00:20:10.376 --> 00:20:12.294
I've ordered labs and X-rays.
- Who are you seeing her with?

515
00:20:12.336 --> 00:20:13.754
- I still need
to present the case.

516
00:20:13.796 --> 00:20:17.049
- Get busy. Find somebody
with MD after their name.

517
00:20:18.676 --> 00:20:21.345
Oh. God. kids.

518
00:20:21.429 --> 00:20:24.140
[indistinct chatter]
- Hello. I'm Dr. Robby.

519
00:20:24.223 --> 00:20:25.766
This is Dr. Santos.

520
00:20:25.808 --> 00:20:27.184
- Chantal.
- How do you do?

521
00:20:27.268 --> 00:20:28.561
We've been caring
for your brother.

522
00:20:28.644 --> 00:20:30.271
- Are you
Jude's legal guardian?

523
00:20:30.354 --> 00:20:31.439
- Yeah.

524
00:20:31.522 --> 00:20:33.983
Our. uh--our parents
aren't around.

525
00:20:34.024 --> 00:20:36.318
Is he going to be okay?
- He got very lucky.

526
00:20:36.402 --> 00:20:38.154
He lost the fourth
and fifth fingers

527
00:20:38.237 --> 00:20:39.655
on his nondominant hand.

528
00:20:39.739 --> 00:20:41.157
But if he hadn't dropped
the firecracker.

529
00:20:41.198 --> 00:20:42.491
it would have been a lot worse.

530
00:20:42.533 --> 00:20:45.161
- He lost fingers
from a firecracker?

531
00:20:45.202 --> 00:20:47.163
Will he be able
to use his hand?

532
00:20:47.246 --> 00:20:49.832
- Yes. he still has his
three most important fingers.

533
00:20:49.874 --> 00:20:51.333
and they are fully functional.

534
00:20:51.417 --> 00:20:53.419
- He'll need surgery
to clean everything up.

535
00:20:53.502 --> 00:20:55.004
but it should heal well.

536
00:20:55.045 --> 00:20:57.131
- What the fuck
were you thinking?

537
00:20:57.214 --> 00:20:58.132
- I'm sorry.

538
00:20:58.215 --> 00:20:59.800
Alex asked me to come over.

539
00:20:59.884 --> 00:21:02.011
His brother had
a stack of fire--

540
00:21:02.094 --> 00:21:05.347
- [speaking Haitian Creole]

541
00:21:05.431 --> 00:21:07.308
- You think I wanted
to blow my hand off?

542
00:21:07.391 --> 00:21:09.560
- Then you need to listen to me
when I tell you something.

543
00:21:09.643 --> 00:21:10.811
- You're not my mom.

544
00:21:10.895 --> 00:21:12.313
- You think I want
to be your mom?

545
00:21:12.396 --> 00:21:15.191
- Chantal. why don't
we take a step outside?

546
00:21:15.232 --> 00:21:17.902
[door opens]

547
00:21:17.985 --> 00:21:20.696
So I know that this can be
very stressful.

548
00:21:20.738 --> 00:21:22.656
- Yeah. he almost lost
his hand being stupid.

549
00:21:22.740 --> 00:21:24.742
- He's a really sweet kid.
- He used to be.

550
00:21:24.825 --> 00:21:27.036
- We also found something
in his blood work.

551
00:21:27.077 --> 00:21:28.245
- What?

552
00:21:28.329 --> 00:21:30.706
- He has a blood alcohol
of 0.08.

553
00:21:30.790 --> 00:21:33.834
- [scoffs]
What. he was drunk?

554
00:21:33.876 --> 00:21:35.461
Are you fucking kidding me?

555
00:21:35.544 --> 00:21:38.047
- Does he drink regularly?
- No.

556
00:21:38.130 --> 00:21:41.008
I...
I don't know. I--

557
00:21:41.091 --> 00:21:43.052
The boys
at our apartment complex

558
00:21:43.135 --> 00:21:44.887
are a really bad influence.

559
00:21:44.970 --> 00:21:46.138
I mean. he's only 12.

560
00:21:46.222 --> 00:21:48.057
- That is what concerns us.

561
00:21:48.098 --> 00:21:49.391
A positive blood alcohol

562
00:21:49.433 --> 00:21:51.352
immediately triggers
a social service consult.

563
00:21:51.435 --> 00:21:52.895
- They gonna take
my brother away from me?

564
00:21:52.978 --> 00:21:54.688
- It's an evaluation
to determine if the injury

565
00:21:54.772 --> 00:21:56.899
and the drinking is cause
for some kind of intervention.

566
00:21:56.941 --> 00:21:59.693
- Whoa. whoa.
I won't let you separate us.

567
00:21:59.777 --> 00:22:01.862
- We are required to--
- No!

568
00:22:08.828 --> 00:22:09.870
- Hmm.

569
00:22:09.954 --> 00:22:11.580
- 58-year-old woman
with nausea.

570
00:22:11.622 --> 00:22:13.791
vomited once after eating warm
potato salad at a barbecue.

571
00:22:13.874 --> 00:22:15.584
Well-hydrated--
abdomen's pretty benign.

572
00:22:15.626 --> 00:22:17.795
just a little distended
with mild tenderness.

573
00:22:17.878 --> 00:22:20.047
History of constipation.
I give her Zofran.

574
00:22:20.089 --> 00:22:21.799
Labs and abdominal
series pending.

575
00:22:21.882 --> 00:22:24.051
- Okay. let's take a look.
- Okay.

576
00:22:24.134 --> 00:22:25.386
Hi. Mrs. Burns.

577
00:22:25.427 --> 00:22:28.222
This is Dr. Whitaker.
How are you feeling?

578
00:22:28.305 --> 00:22:30.224
Mrs. Burns?

579
00:22:30.307 --> 00:22:32.434
- Mrs. Burns. can you open
your eyes for me?

580
00:22:32.518 --> 00:22:34.436
- She was awake and alert
last time I saw her.

581
00:22:34.478 --> 00:22:37.106
- Okay. uh. feels warm.
thready pulse.

582
00:22:37.147 --> 00:22:38.899
- Abdomen's more distended
than before.

583
00:22:38.983 --> 00:22:41.068
- Okay. uh.
agonal respirations.

584
00:22:41.110 --> 00:22:43.028
She's--she's hardly breathing.
- It's kind of rigid.

585
00:22:43.112 --> 00:22:45.197
- Yeah. yeah. Perlah.
we need a crash cart.

586
00:22:45.281 --> 00:22:46.699
Can you call respiratory?

587
00:22:46.782 --> 00:22:48.909
- Pull the bed out
for intubation. please.

588
00:22:48.993 --> 00:22:51.120
- I can give you
guys some room.

589
00:22:51.203 --> 00:22:52.621
- Okay.
- What's up?

590
00:22:52.705 --> 00:22:55.124
- Hypotensive. acute abdomen.
She needs an airway.

591
00:22:55.165 --> 00:22:57.293
- I'll find the GlideScope.
- No time for that.

592
00:22:57.334 --> 00:22:58.794
We've got direct
on the crash cart.

593
00:22:58.836 --> 00:23:00.713
Whitaker. you're up.
- I haven't done many directs.

594
00:23:00.796 --> 00:23:02.131
- Well. then you need
to do more.

595
00:23:02.214 --> 00:23:04.133
Induction meds?
- 100 ketamine. 80 of raw.

596
00:23:04.174 --> 00:23:06.635
- Javadi. what's the story?

597
00:23:06.719 --> 00:23:08.637
- Presented
with mild abdominal pain.

598
00:23:08.679 --> 00:23:11.515
took a turn for the worse.
[device beeping rapidly]

599
00:23:11.599 --> 00:23:14.268
- A-fib 122.
BP 98 and systolic.

600
00:23:14.351 --> 00:23:15.811
- Okay. let's bolus
another 500 cc's.

601
00:23:15.895 --> 00:23:18.272
- Are we shocking her?
- Uh. maybe. After intubation.

602
00:23:18.355 --> 00:23:19.857
Check your light.
Check your balloon.

603
00:23:19.940 --> 00:23:21.984
Javadi. AP pads in case
we need to cardiovert.

604
00:23:22.026 --> 00:23:24.194
- Normal EKG at triage.
She wasn't in A-fib.

605
00:23:24.278 --> 00:23:26.655
- Stress from her condition
probably put her there.

606
00:23:26.697 --> 00:23:27.990
Good?
Let's roll her.

607
00:23:28.073 --> 00:23:30.326
Do we have any labs back?
- I don't think so.

608
00:23:30.409 --> 00:23:32.661
- What else do we need?
- Um. blood cultures.

609
00:23:32.745 --> 00:23:35.164
Lactate. 2 liters LR.
3.375 pip-tazo.

610
00:23:35.247 --> 00:23:36.415
- Okay. she's loose.

611
00:23:36.498 --> 00:23:38.667
Go ahead. Whitaker.
Take a look.

612
00:23:38.709 --> 00:23:41.962
- Okay.
[beeping continues]

613
00:23:46.717 --> 00:23:49.511
- Hi. I'm Dr. Santos.
This is student doctor Kwon.

614
00:23:49.595 --> 00:23:51.180
How are you doing
after the mist?

615
00:23:51.221 --> 00:23:52.848
- Better than I was
an hour ago.

616
00:23:52.932 --> 00:23:56.644
- Okay. we are going
to check your vitals.

617
00:23:56.727 --> 00:23:57.853
[device beeps]

618
00:23:57.895 --> 00:24:02.274
- Temp is 100.2.
and heart rate is 96.

619
00:24:02.358 --> 00:24:04.693
- Okay. down
from 101.5 and 120.

620
00:24:04.777 --> 00:24:06.236
Very good.

621
00:24:06.320 --> 00:24:08.572
- You were out in the heat
in that costume?

622
00:24:08.656 --> 00:24:11.533
- Yeah. with about 18.000
of my friends.

623
00:24:11.617 --> 00:24:13.869
- Were you at Anthrocon?
- Uh-huh.

624
00:24:13.911 --> 00:24:15.204
- What's that?

625
00:24:15.287 --> 00:24:17.247
- Pittsburgh's annual
furry convention.

626
00:24:17.331 --> 00:24:18.874
I go every year.

627
00:24:18.916 --> 00:24:20.542
Ever been?

628
00:24:20.584 --> 00:24:23.379
- Uh. it's not really my scene.
- Mm.

629
00:24:23.420 --> 00:24:24.755
Yeah. furries get a bad rap.

630
00:24:24.838 --> 00:24:27.716
but there are great people
in the community--

631
00:24:27.800 --> 00:24:31.220
creative. welcoming. funny.

632
00:24:31.303 --> 00:24:34.056
I actually met my girlfriend
at last year's convention.

633
00:24:34.098 --> 00:24:35.683
- Oh. that's cute.

634
00:24:35.724 --> 00:24:38.477
- She gave me hope after
struggling on the dating apps.

635
00:24:38.560 --> 00:24:39.728
- Nice to hear

636
00:24:39.812 --> 00:24:42.189
that meeting people
in real life still works.

637
00:24:42.272 --> 00:24:44.984
- Wouldn't recommend it.
especially at work.

638
00:24:45.067 --> 00:24:48.070
- You should come
to Anthrocon this weekend.

639
00:24:48.112 --> 00:24:50.489
- Doesn't she need
a fur suit for that?

640
00:24:50.572 --> 00:24:53.117
- I think you'd make
a good dragon.

641
00:24:56.412 --> 00:24:57.705
- I'm in.

642
00:24:57.788 --> 00:24:58.998
Balloon up.

643
00:24:59.081 --> 00:25:01.750
[rapid beeping continues]
Yep. bag her.

644
00:25:01.792 --> 00:25:03.335
Okay.

645
00:25:03.419 --> 00:25:06.213
That was harder without video.
- We won't always have video.

646
00:25:06.296 --> 00:25:07.381
- A-fib now at 152.

647
00:25:07.464 --> 00:25:09.258
Blood pressure's
down to 76 over 44.

648
00:25:09.341 --> 00:25:13.429
- Okay. Javadi. sync mode.
Javadi. sync mode. 200. please.

649
00:25:13.512 --> 00:25:15.431
- Good end tidal waveform.

650
00:25:15.472 --> 00:25:17.766
- Good breath sounds
bilaterally.

651
00:25:17.808 --> 00:25:20.269
[machine whirs]
- Charged for cardioversion.

652
00:25:20.352 --> 00:25:22.813
- Everyone. clear.

653
00:25:22.896 --> 00:25:24.982
[thump. machine beeps]

654
00:25:25.065 --> 00:25:27.901
- Normal sinus.
- Normal radial pulse.

655
00:25:27.985 --> 00:25:29.236
- [exhales sharply]

656
00:25:29.319 --> 00:25:30.988
- Good.
Keep the fluids going.

657
00:25:31.071 --> 00:25:33.574
Let's see what labs
are back on her.

658
00:25:35.409 --> 00:25:36.452
- Nice.

659
00:25:36.535 --> 00:25:39.121
- [sighs]
- Very nice.

660
00:25:39.204 --> 00:25:42.249
- What did you order?
- Um. CBC. ER chem panel.

661
00:25:42.291 --> 00:25:44.793
- Something should be back.
- Fax machine ran out of toner.

662
00:25:44.877 --> 00:25:47.463
Check the chart.
- There is no chart in slot 22.

663
00:25:47.504 --> 00:25:49.965
- Check the orders rack.

664
00:25:50.007 --> 00:25:51.467
- Nothing here either.

665
00:25:51.550 --> 00:25:54.011
- Where's the chart
for Claire Burns?

666
00:25:55.888 --> 00:25:57.306
- Claire Burns. order slip.

667
00:25:57.347 --> 00:25:58.932
Never drawn.
never sent off to the lab.

668
00:25:59.016 --> 00:26:00.642
- That's cause the patient
wasn't on the board.

669
00:26:00.726 --> 00:26:02.227
Nurses are working zones.

670
00:26:02.311 --> 00:26:03.979
If the patient's not
on the board. they don't exist.

671
00:26:04.063 --> 00:26:05.647
- So they didn't shoot
her X-ray?

672
00:26:05.689 --> 00:26:07.941
- X-ray downtime box is empty.
That means it was done.

673
00:26:08.025 --> 00:26:09.651
- Then it's
on the portable machine.

674
00:26:09.735 --> 00:26:11.987
- Last I saw.
it was headed north.

675
00:26:12.029 --> 00:26:13.822
- Thanks. Dana.
- Yep.

676
00:26:13.906 --> 00:26:15.699
- Hey. Kenny.
can you wait up a sec?

677
00:26:15.783 --> 00:26:17.159
- If you need an X-ray.
write the order.

678
00:26:17.242 --> 00:26:18.368
Fill out a downtime.

679
00:26:18.452 --> 00:26:20.120
- Did you shoot a KUB
in South 22?

680
00:26:20.204 --> 00:26:21.497
- No.
Maybe another tech did?

681
00:26:21.538 --> 00:26:23.165
- Okay. can you flick
through the films.

682
00:26:23.207 --> 00:26:25.209
look for a patient--Burns?

683
00:26:28.587 --> 00:26:29.797
- Oh. shit.

684
00:26:29.838 --> 00:26:31.673
- Oh. that is a classic
sigmoid volvulus.

685
00:26:31.715 --> 00:26:33.675
- Peritoneal signs.
- Okay. call the OR.

686
00:26:33.717 --> 00:26:36.553
She's going to need
surgery ASAP.

687
00:26:43.727 --> 00:26:45.771
- Urine shows three plus blood.

688
00:26:45.854 --> 00:26:47.689
- No surprise.

689
00:26:47.731 --> 00:26:49.691
- BUN and creatinine
are normal.

690
00:26:49.775 --> 00:26:51.360
No evidence
of renal insufficiency.

691
00:26:51.443 --> 00:26:53.153
I got a good look
at the left kidney--

692
00:26:53.237 --> 00:26:56.323
mild hydronephrosis consistent
with ureteral column.

693
00:26:56.406 --> 00:26:58.617
- How was the rest
of the ultrasound?

694
00:26:58.700 --> 00:27:01.954
- Normal. Uh. Pain improved
after 15 ketorolac IM.

695
00:27:02.037 --> 00:27:04.665
- Now you can give
another 15 and observe.

696
00:27:04.748 --> 00:27:07.292
- Hmm.

697
00:27:07.376 --> 00:27:10.087
Just need you
to cosign my order.

698
00:27:11.922 --> 00:27:13.048
Thank you.

699
00:27:13.090 --> 00:27:15.717
- [sighs]
- Something on your mind?

700
00:27:15.801 --> 00:27:18.387
- Yeah. I-I saw this regular
an hour ago.

701
00:27:18.428 --> 00:27:20.097
He's in his 60s.
fakes an ailment

702
00:27:20.180 --> 00:27:22.558
so he can come in to chat
every now and then

703
00:27:22.641 --> 00:27:24.268
because he's really lonely.

704
00:27:24.351 --> 00:27:26.436
- You sure he just doesn't have
a crush on you?

705
00:27:26.520 --> 00:27:29.231
- Maybe. but it got me thinking
about my mom.

706
00:27:29.314 --> 00:27:31.942
She's probably
just been lonely.

707
00:27:32.025 --> 00:27:34.111
- Yeah.

708
00:27:34.194 --> 00:27:35.571
You know. I. uh...

709
00:27:35.654 --> 00:27:38.240
I haven't really dated
since my divorce.

710
00:27:38.323 --> 00:27:40.576
Medical school.
my kid. residency.

711
00:27:40.659 --> 00:27:43.245
And now I'm feeling
finally kind of ready.

712
00:27:43.287 --> 00:27:45.205
- I was waiting
until I got back to Jersey

713
00:27:45.289 --> 00:27:47.040
to work on finding
a relationship.

714
00:27:47.124 --> 00:27:48.584
and now that's out the window.

715
00:27:48.667 --> 00:27:50.752
Maybe I waited too long.

716
00:27:50.836 --> 00:27:51.920
- For what?

717
00:27:52.004 --> 00:27:53.755
- Do you hear that?

718
00:27:53.797 --> 00:27:58.093
That painful. lonely silence
is the sound of my eggs dying.

719
00:27:58.135 --> 00:28:00.846
- [chuckles]

720
00:28:00.929 --> 00:28:02.222
[bell dings]
- Ah.

721
00:28:02.264 --> 00:28:04.224
So the rash in North 3
has been discharged.

722
00:28:04.308 --> 00:28:06.101
The Tasered law student
in Central 10

723
00:28:06.185 --> 00:28:07.436
has gone up to psych.

724
00:28:07.477 --> 00:28:09.188
The eye stroke is
now in the ICU.

725
00:28:09.271 --> 00:28:10.898
And the tongue laceration
in South 15

726
00:28:10.981 --> 00:28:12.524
is sobering up
before we discharge.

727
00:28:12.608 --> 00:28:14.443
which better be soon
because we need the room.

728
00:28:14.484 --> 00:28:15.611
- Okay. I'll grab a med student

729
00:28:15.694 --> 00:28:17.112
and get more patients
moving out.

730
00:28:17.196 --> 00:28:19.072
- You're not fazed
by any of this chaos?

731
00:28:19.156 --> 00:28:21.074
- Hmm.
- What a fucking mess.

732
00:28:21.158 --> 00:28:24.119
- Jesus Christ. we need you.

733
00:28:24.161 --> 00:28:27.581
Monica Peters. this is our new
attending. Dr. Al-Hashimi.

734
00:28:27.664 --> 00:28:29.333
- Welcome.
- Thank you.

735
00:28:29.416 --> 00:28:31.418
- Monica's a retired clerk.
best of the best.

736
00:28:31.501 --> 00:28:33.462
She was kind enough
to come in on a holiday

737
00:28:33.503 --> 00:28:35.005
and help get us
back into shape.

738
00:28:35.088 --> 00:28:36.840
- Laid off
by the digital revolution.

739
00:28:36.924 --> 00:28:38.467
not retired.
- Okay.

740
00:28:38.550 --> 00:28:41.094
- And how's all this digital
shit working out for you now?

741
00:28:41.178 --> 00:28:43.305
- Not so good.
- Exactly.

742
00:28:43.388 --> 00:28:45.182
All right. then.
who's handling

743
00:28:45.265 --> 00:28:47.643
the charts and the orders?
- That's us. right here.

744
00:28:47.726 --> 00:28:49.478
- How long have
you been clerks?

745
00:28:49.519 --> 00:28:51.897
- Uh. just today.
We're medical assistants.

746
00:28:51.980 --> 00:28:53.232
- Then get out of my space

747
00:28:53.315 --> 00:28:55.484
and go do something
you know how to do.

748
00:28:55.567 --> 00:28:56.818
And no personal calls.

749
00:28:56.902 --> 00:28:58.820
Red phones are
for emergencies only.

750
00:28:58.862 --> 00:29:00.614
This is a hospital.
for God's sake.

751
00:29:00.697 --> 00:29:01.657
- I'll call you back.

752
00:29:01.740 --> 00:29:02.991
- Got a gumband?
- Yeah.

753
00:29:03.075 --> 00:29:04.785
- Hi. I'm Makedah
from admin and records.

754
00:29:04.868 --> 00:29:06.828
I have a new badge
for a Dr. Whitaker.

755
00:29:06.912 --> 00:29:08.914
- Yeah.
I'll get that to him.

756
00:29:08.997 --> 00:29:10.666
- Heard you all
need extra runners?

757
00:29:10.749 --> 00:29:12.626
- Perfect timing.
- How fast can you move?

758
00:29:12.709 --> 00:29:14.336
- I run marathons.
- Great.

759
00:29:14.378 --> 00:29:17.172
Grab the blood samples and the
bin and get them up to the lab.

760
00:29:17.256 --> 00:29:19.675
I want a lab run
every 15 minutes.

761
00:29:19.716 --> 00:29:21.176
- Got it.

762
00:29:21.218 --> 00:29:24.388
[indistinct chatter]

763
00:29:26.390 --> 00:29:28.392
- I work at a shoe store
in Oakland.

764
00:29:28.475 --> 00:29:30.394
- Full-time
and you're in school?

765
00:29:30.477 --> 00:29:31.979
- Yes. and. yes.

766
00:29:32.062 --> 00:29:33.647
Allegheny Community.

767
00:29:33.730 --> 00:29:35.983
- Does Jude go
to summer school or camp

768
00:29:36.066 --> 00:29:39.987
while you're
at. uh. work or school?

769
00:29:40.070 --> 00:29:41.989
- Can't afford it.

770
00:29:42.072 --> 00:29:43.573
- Are there any other
family members

771
00:29:43.657 --> 00:29:46.034
that could help with his care
when you're not available?

772
00:29:46.076 --> 00:29:47.411
- No.

773
00:29:50.580 --> 00:29:51.873
- Chantal. we want to help you.

774
00:29:51.915 --> 00:29:54.501
but we can't help
if you won't talk to us.

775
00:29:54.543 --> 00:29:56.545
- What. you're
gonna take Jude away

776
00:29:56.628 --> 00:29:58.380
and put him in foster care?

777
00:29:58.422 --> 00:30:01.383
I promised my parents
that would never happen.

778
00:30:01.466 --> 00:30:03.719
- Did your parents pass away?

779
00:30:03.802 --> 00:30:05.178
- Nope.

780
00:30:05.262 --> 00:30:08.807
- What happened to them?
- [sighs]

781
00:30:13.312 --> 00:30:16.648
- My parents were deported
to Haiti nine months ago.

782
00:30:16.732 --> 00:30:19.192
[breathes shakily]

783
00:30:19.276 --> 00:30:22.237
They went in for their
immigration hearing and were...

784
00:30:22.321 --> 00:30:24.573
detained.

785
00:30:24.614 --> 00:30:26.450
I was a sophomore at Ithaca.

786
00:30:26.533 --> 00:30:30.120
I had to move back home
to take care of my brother.

787
00:30:30.203 --> 00:30:31.788
- I'm sorry.

788
00:30:31.872 --> 00:30:36.418
- It was either that. or he
moved back to Haiti with them.

789
00:30:36.501 --> 00:30:38.962
He's never been there.

790
00:30:39.046 --> 00:30:41.465
We were both born here.

791
00:30:43.133 --> 00:30:47.429
[scoffs] My mom was so excited
when I got into college.

792
00:30:47.512 --> 00:30:49.598
She worked so hard

793
00:30:49.639 --> 00:30:52.559
to save up and pay my tuition.

794
00:30:52.642 --> 00:30:54.561
And now all she wants

795
00:30:54.644 --> 00:30:57.064
is for my brother
to finish high school.

796
00:30:58.982 --> 00:31:01.026
Man. being a big sister's
a lot easier

797
00:31:01.109 --> 00:31:03.070
than being a surrogate mom.

798
00:31:05.655 --> 00:31:07.366
- Just give us a moment.
please.

799
00:31:07.449 --> 00:31:09.910
and I'll come grab you
when we're done.

800
00:31:13.372 --> 00:31:15.874
- Do we really need to get
family services involved?

801
00:31:15.957 --> 00:31:17.959
- You wanted to get
them involved this morning

802
00:31:18.001 --> 00:31:20.128
with your eight-year-old
ITP patient.

803
00:31:20.212 --> 00:31:22.798
- That's different.
Abuse trumps neglect.

804
00:31:22.839 --> 00:31:24.674
We can't separate her
from her brother.

805
00:31:24.758 --> 00:31:26.301
It's not right.

806
00:31:26.343 --> 00:31:29.096
- A lot of what happens to
people around here isn't right.

807
00:31:31.932 --> 00:31:33.683
[person groaning]

808
00:31:33.767 --> 00:31:36.770
- McKay. patient's
complaining of pain.

809
00:31:36.853 --> 00:31:39.648
- Uh. yeah.

810
00:31:39.689 --> 00:31:42.359
Hey. Amaya.
What's going on?

811
00:31:42.442 --> 00:31:44.152
- Oh. it really
fucking hurts again.

812
00:31:44.236 --> 00:31:46.154
- Hey. Jesse.
can you grab Whitaker?

813
00:31:46.238 --> 00:31:48.698
When did it get bad?
- Two minutes ago. Aah!

814
00:31:48.782 --> 00:31:50.826
- Giving you some morphine
to take the edge off.

815
00:31:50.867 --> 00:31:54.329
How severe. 1 to 10?
- Ah. 12. It's way worse.

816
00:31:54.371 --> 00:31:55.664
- Okay.

817
00:31:55.705 --> 00:31:57.624
Hey. Amaya. the meds
will kick in.

818
00:31:57.707 --> 00:31:59.584
and we'll get you back
on the foot rest

819
00:31:59.668 --> 00:32:02.754
to see what's going on. okay?
- [groaning]

820
00:32:02.838 --> 00:32:05.465
[door opens. closes]

821
00:32:05.549 --> 00:32:09.010
- I had to call her husband
in New York to get consent.

822
00:32:09.052 --> 00:32:10.011
- Okay.

823
00:32:10.095 --> 00:32:12.514
- Dr. Shamsi
will be operating.

824
00:32:12.556 --> 00:32:14.516
If she presented
with peritoneal signs.

825
00:32:14.558 --> 00:32:16.101
why wasn't I called?

826
00:32:16.184 --> 00:32:18.812
- There was
a delayed presentation.

827
00:32:18.895 --> 00:32:20.522
- The X-ray was shot
an hour ago.

828
00:32:20.564 --> 00:32:22.023
Why didn't anybody read it?

829
00:32:22.107 --> 00:32:23.984
- There was confusion
with the digital systems down.

830
00:32:24.067 --> 00:32:25.652
It wasn't read.
We didn't get a report.

831
00:32:25.735 --> 00:32:28.363
- An hour ago. I could have
fixed this in 60 seconds

832
00:32:28.447 --> 00:32:30.031
with a rectal tube.

833
00:32:30.073 --> 00:32:31.700
Now she needs major surgery.

834
00:32:31.741 --> 00:32:34.536
- I'm sorry.
- Not good enough. nepo baby.

835
00:32:34.619 --> 00:32:36.163
You fucked up.

836
00:32:36.204 --> 00:32:38.707
Don't trust anything or anybody
else when the system's down.

837
00:32:38.748 --> 00:32:40.208
[elevator bell dings]

838
00:32:40.250 --> 00:32:43.753
- With all the chaos. she
just fell through the cracks.

839
00:32:45.338 --> 00:32:48.091
- She almost died.

840
00:32:48.175 --> 00:32:49.885
I could have killed her.

841
00:32:49.926 --> 00:32:51.720
- Whitaker.
- No--

842
00:32:51.761 --> 00:32:54.222
- McKay needs you
in Central 11.

843
00:32:54.264 --> 00:32:55.849
- We caught it in time.

844
00:32:55.932 --> 00:32:58.435
We won't let it
happen again. okay?

845
00:33:09.779 --> 00:33:12.240
- Oh. uh. Princess
is looking for you.

846
00:33:12.324 --> 00:33:15.410
Um. she said something
about Monica under her breath.

847
00:33:15.494 --> 00:33:18.914
but I couldn't make it out.
- Okay. I'll be back in a sec.

848
00:33:18.955 --> 00:33:21.708
Hey. Hey.

849
00:33:21.791 --> 00:33:25.420
You did good with that
sexual-assault victim.

850
00:33:25.504 --> 00:33:27.547
- You were amazing with her.

851
00:33:27.631 --> 00:33:29.633
- We do what we can to provide
the best care

852
00:33:29.716 --> 00:33:33.094
to traumatized people
in their darkest days.

853
00:33:33.136 --> 00:33:34.471
What'd you talk to her about

854
00:33:34.554 --> 00:33:36.473
when you took her out
on the walk?

855
00:33:36.556 --> 00:33:38.642
- I. um...

856
00:33:38.725 --> 00:33:40.644
told her there might be a time
in the future

857
00:33:40.727 --> 00:33:45.607
when she changes her mind.
wants to press charges.

858
00:33:45.649 --> 00:33:48.443
It's better to have
the option to do it than not.

859
00:33:48.527 --> 00:33:50.820
- Smart.

860
00:33:52.864 --> 00:33:54.449
- Is every day like this?

861
00:33:54.491 --> 00:33:58.578
- Minus the cyberattacks. yeah.

862
00:33:58.662 --> 00:34:00.580
But you're only
a few hours away

863
00:34:00.664 --> 00:34:03.250
from being done
with your first of many.

864
00:34:03.333 --> 00:34:04.626
Be proud of that.

865
00:34:04.709 --> 00:34:07.921
[distant train horn blowing]

866
00:34:11.675 --> 00:34:13.760
- You're gonna want to be
on a soft diet.

867
00:34:13.802 --> 00:34:16.804
so. uh. things
like. uh. mashed potatoes.

868
00:34:16.888 --> 00:34:18.889
soup. mac and cheese are good.

869
00:34:18.974 --> 00:34:20.475
- I was gonna make

870
00:34:20.516 --> 00:34:22.310
your favorite
three-bean dip tonight.

871
00:34:22.393 --> 00:34:24.271
- [lisping]
Bitch. that is so nice.

872
00:34:24.353 --> 00:34:25.647
- See. I am nice.

873
00:34:25.730 --> 00:34:27.399
Could she have that?

874
00:34:27.482 --> 00:34:30.360
- Uh. yeah. Yeah. yeah.
if you eat it with a spoon

875
00:34:30.443 --> 00:34:32.112
rather than anything.
like. crunchy

876
00:34:32.195 --> 00:34:34.322
that could work its way
into the laceration.

877
00:34:34.364 --> 00:34:35.322
both:
Mm.

878
00:34:35.364 --> 00:34:37.033
- So she'll need
to be spoon-fed?

879
00:34:37.117 --> 00:34:38.326
- [chuckles]

880
00:34:38.409 --> 00:34:40.328
- Antibiotics
three times a day.

881
00:34:40.411 --> 00:34:42.455
Come back here in two days
for a wound check.

882
00:34:42.539 --> 00:34:45.667
- See you then. Doctor.

883
00:34:45.750 --> 00:34:49.504
- Checking blood flow
to the ovary.

884
00:34:53.675 --> 00:34:56.511
- Something wrong?
- Intermittent torsion.

885
00:34:56.553 --> 00:34:58.179
- What's that?

886
00:34:58.221 --> 00:35:00.640
- I'm coming out now.

887
00:35:00.724 --> 00:35:02.851
We will slide you back.
Thanks.

888
00:35:02.892 --> 00:35:06.438
- [sighs deeply]
- Your ovary is twisting

889
00:35:06.521 --> 00:35:08.148
and cutting off
the blood supply.

890
00:35:08.231 --> 00:35:10.191
That's what's been causing
your pain.

891
00:35:10.233 --> 00:35:13.695
- Ah. You said the blood supply
was fine before.

892
00:35:13.778 --> 00:35:17.324
- Sometimes the ovary
can twist randomly.

893
00:35:17.365 --> 00:35:20.827
- In those cases.
the pain can come and go.

894
00:35:20.910 --> 00:35:23.955
- Can you fix it?
- With surgery.

895
00:35:24.039 --> 00:35:25.206
- "Surgery"?

896
00:35:25.290 --> 00:35:27.042
- The ovary needs
to be untwisted

897
00:35:27.125 --> 00:35:30.045
and tacked down with a stitch
so this doesn't happen again.

898
00:35:30.128 --> 00:35:33.506
If we can get you upstairs
quickly. we can save it.

899
00:35:33.590 --> 00:35:36.009
- I could lose my ovary?

900
00:35:36.092 --> 00:35:37.927
Will I still be able
to have a baby?

901
00:35:38.011 --> 00:35:40.180
- This shouldn't be
an issue in the future.

902
00:35:40.263 --> 00:35:41.848
- Dr. McKay made the right call

903
00:35:41.931 --> 00:35:43.933
to keep you in the ER
for observation

904
00:35:44.017 --> 00:35:47.729
so we could catch it
if the pain returned.

905
00:35:47.812 --> 00:35:49.230
- Thank you.

906
00:35:49.314 --> 00:35:52.108
- I'll call GYN.
- Yeah.

907
00:35:52.192 --> 00:35:53.902
[bell dings]

908
00:35:53.943 --> 00:35:55.904
- Hey. welcome back.
How was the trip?

909
00:35:55.945 --> 00:35:57.906
- Smooth sailing.
Presby's pretty nice.

910
00:35:57.989 --> 00:36:00.617
I might have to pick up
some day shifts over there.

911
00:36:00.700 --> 00:36:02.702
- [electronic voice]
Dr. Abbot's funny.

912
00:36:02.786 --> 00:36:04.663
- Trust me.
his charm wears off.

913
00:36:04.746 --> 00:36:06.247
- No. it doesn't.
- He's not sedated?

914
00:36:06.331 --> 00:36:08.583
- I gave him Versed for
the CT scan on the ride back.

915
00:36:08.625 --> 00:36:10.543
but I figured he'd need to be
awake and alert

916
00:36:10.627 --> 00:36:11.836
to give consent.
- "Consent"?

917
00:36:11.920 --> 00:36:13.421
- Yep.
We're going to get you settled.

918
00:36:13.505 --> 00:36:15.507
Why don't you page Garcia
to come down?

919
00:36:15.590 --> 00:36:17.258
- Dr. Robby.
- You got this?

920
00:36:17.342 --> 00:36:19.427
- You know I got it.
- Yep.

921
00:36:19.511 --> 00:36:21.513
- All right. Howard.

922
00:36:21.596 --> 00:36:23.682
- Hey. I want to debrief
with you later

923
00:36:23.765 --> 00:36:25.100
on your sigmoid volvulus
patient.

924
00:36:25.183 --> 00:36:26.935
- I finished with your
fireworks kid's sister.

925
00:36:26.976 --> 00:36:28.269
- And?
- She's a responsible

926
00:36:28.353 --> 00:36:29.938
young woman
and a good guardian to Jude.

927
00:36:30.021 --> 00:36:32.190
There is no reason to get
family services involved today.

928
00:36:32.273 --> 00:36:33.608
- That's good.

929
00:36:33.650 --> 00:36:35.235
- Because he's
in the hospital for surgery.

930
00:36:35.318 --> 00:36:37.237
but they will most likely make
a home visit next week

931
00:36:37.320 --> 00:36:38.905
to evaluate the safety
of their apartment

932
00:36:38.988 --> 00:36:40.448
and the care
that Chantal can provide.

933
00:36:40.532 --> 00:36:42.117
along with her
other responsibilities.

934
00:36:42.158 --> 00:36:43.785
- And then what?
They take Jude?

935
00:36:43.868 --> 00:36:46.079
- In my experience. they'll
make the same assessment I did.

936
00:36:46.162 --> 00:36:47.789
They don't like
to separate siblings.

937
00:36:47.872 --> 00:36:49.624
- Anything else
we can do for 'em?

938
00:36:49.666 --> 00:36:51.501
- I'll get some resources
together for Chantal--

939
00:36:51.584 --> 00:36:53.128
summer after-school programs.

940
00:36:53.169 --> 00:36:55.130
But there might come a point
when he'd be better off

941
00:36:55.171 --> 00:36:56.339
with his parents in Haiti.

942
00:36:56.423 --> 00:36:57.799
- His parents want him
to stay here.

943
00:36:57.882 --> 00:36:59.300
- It's what's best
for the child.

944
00:36:59.384 --> 00:37:00.969
- Says who?
- Dr. Santos.

945
00:37:01.010 --> 00:37:02.262
Come on.

946
00:37:04.055 --> 00:37:06.266
- Welcome back. Mr. Knox.
What did we discover?

947
00:37:06.307 --> 00:37:08.935
- Diverticular abscess
that progressed to perforation.

948
00:37:09.018 --> 00:37:10.812
now with free air
under the diaphragm.

949
00:37:10.854 --> 00:37:12.647
- [electronic voice]
In English. please?

950
00:37:12.689 --> 00:37:14.315
- There's a small hole
in the colon

951
00:37:14.357 --> 00:37:15.984
that's spilling bacteria
into the abdomen.

952
00:37:16.067 --> 00:37:19.946
- You're likely to develop
peritonitis and sepsis.

953
00:37:20.029 --> 00:37:21.614
- [electronic voice]
How bad?

954
00:37:21.698 --> 00:37:23.074
- You need surgery now.

955
00:37:23.158 --> 00:37:26.786
You have a 100% chance
of death without it.

956
00:37:26.870 --> 00:37:28.455
- [electronic voice]
With it?

957
00:37:30.665 --> 00:37:32.709
- 50% chance.

958
00:37:35.336 --> 00:37:36.796
- [electronic voice]
I could die?

959
00:37:36.880 --> 00:37:38.965
- Yes. but we're very good
at what we do.

960
00:37:39.007 --> 00:37:41.885
- That is what
the consent is for.

961
00:37:41.968 --> 00:37:43.803
- [electronic voice]
What about my sister?

962
00:37:43.887 --> 00:37:46.347
- We found her.
She'd like to speak with you.

963
00:37:46.431 --> 00:37:48.016
- We don't have time for that.

964
00:37:48.099 --> 00:37:50.518
Any delay increases
your mortality risks.

965
00:37:50.602 --> 00:37:53.688
- [electronic voice] I want
to talk to my sister first.

966
00:37:56.983 --> 00:37:59.736
- We're gonna make
that happen for you.

967
00:37:59.819 --> 00:38:03.072
- I'll have them prep an OR.
but make it fast. very fast.

968
00:38:03.156 --> 00:38:06.242
- Yeah. We're on the move
again. Howard.

969
00:38:06.326 --> 00:38:09.496
[indistinct chatter]

970
00:38:20.757 --> 00:38:22.509
- Hey.

971
00:38:24.427 --> 00:38:26.805
The ice cream party over?

972
00:38:28.598 --> 00:38:30.725
- Yes.

973
00:38:30.767 --> 00:38:33.895
- Do you need anything?

974
00:38:33.978 --> 00:38:35.730
- [sighs softly]

975
00:38:35.772 --> 00:38:37.816
A time machine.

976
00:38:41.694 --> 00:38:43.947
- That'd be nice.
wouldn't it?

977
00:38:48.284 --> 00:38:51.412
- I don't even know
what hurts more--

978
00:38:51.454 --> 00:38:54.541
the cancer or...

979
00:38:56.668 --> 00:39:00.171
Knowing I'm never gonna see
my sons grow up.

980
00:39:02.549 --> 00:39:04.968
It feels like a cruel joke.

981
00:39:06.469 --> 00:39:11.057
Why give me children
and a husband I adore

982
00:39:11.140 --> 00:39:14.936
if you're just gonna
take them away from me?

983
00:39:14.978 --> 00:39:18.356
For what?
Fucking lung cancer.

984
00:39:18.439 --> 00:39:21.526
[breathes deeply]

985
00:39:21.609 --> 00:39:23.528
I didn't even smoke.

986
00:39:23.611 --> 00:39:26.823
[breathing heavily]

987
00:39:31.536 --> 00:39:33.663
Do you believe in God?

988
00:39:35.957 --> 00:39:38.167
- I like the concept.

989
00:39:42.046 --> 00:39:45.341
- I'm sure you've seen
a lot of death.

990
00:39:45.425 --> 00:39:47.427
- I have seen my share.

991
00:39:50.179 --> 00:39:52.223
- Any advice?

992
00:39:57.854 --> 00:40:00.607
I've never died before.

993
00:40:09.908 --> 00:40:11.659
- Hey. sorry.
W-we're outside.

994
00:40:11.701 --> 00:40:15.163
There's. um--there's no
cell service inside right now.

995
00:40:15.246 --> 00:40:16.748
but. um. here he is.

996
00:40:19.000 --> 00:40:20.418
- Oh. my God.

997
00:40:20.501 --> 00:40:22.795
Are you all right?

998
00:40:24.047 --> 00:40:25.757
- [electronic voice]
Been better.

999
00:40:25.840 --> 00:40:28.134
You look beautiful.

1000
00:40:28.217 --> 00:40:29.761
- Thank you.

1001
00:40:29.844 --> 00:40:32.055
You're not looking so hot.

1002
00:40:34.182 --> 00:40:36.976
- [electronic voice]
Thank you for calling back.

1003
00:40:39.187 --> 00:40:40.813
- Of course.

1004
00:40:40.897 --> 00:40:43.733
I'm sorry
that it's been this long.

1005
00:40:43.816 --> 00:40:47.320
All the stuff with Dad
and the drinking. I--

1006
00:40:47.403 --> 00:40:50.531
I had to do what was best
for me and Tommy.

1007
00:40:50.573 --> 00:40:53.034
- [electronic voice]
How is Tommy?

1008
00:40:53.076 --> 00:40:56.996
- Starting his junior year
in high school next month.

1009
00:40:57.080 --> 00:41:00.458
16 and already has
a girlfriend.

1010
00:41:02.418 --> 00:41:04.671
- [electronic voice]
Takes after his uncle.

1011
00:41:04.754 --> 00:41:06.714
- [laughs]

1012
00:41:06.798 --> 00:41:08.383
Maybe we can make a plan

1013
00:41:08.466 --> 00:41:11.177
for you to see each other
over the holidays.

1014
00:41:15.390 --> 00:41:17.475
- [electronic voice]
I'd love that.

1015
00:41:18.935 --> 00:41:20.770
- Is the doctor there?

1016
00:41:22.563 --> 00:41:24.023
- Hi. I'm Dr. Abbot.

1017
00:41:24.107 --> 00:41:25.817
- Can you call me
when he gets out of surgery?

1018
00:41:25.900 --> 00:41:28.027
- Of course. but right now we
need to get him up to the OR.

1019
00:41:28.069 --> 00:41:29.570
- I understand.
Thanks.

1020
00:41:29.654 --> 00:41:31.447
Talk to you soon. Howard.

1021
00:41:33.449 --> 00:41:36.911
Oh. I forgot to tell him
I love him.

1022
00:41:36.995 --> 00:41:38.246
- Oh. wow.

1023
00:41:38.287 --> 00:41:40.081
Monica?

1024
00:41:40.164 --> 00:41:41.374
Welcome back.

1025
00:41:41.457 --> 00:41:43.418
- Robinavitch.

1026
00:41:43.501 --> 00:41:46.212
Two for the lab. three for CT.
- I'll take those.

1027
00:41:46.295 --> 00:41:48.923
They need me upstairs.
- On it for CT.

1028
00:41:49.007 --> 00:41:50.258
- You run a tight ship.

1029
00:41:50.299 --> 00:41:52.260
- Well. it's
a work in progress.

1030
00:41:52.343 --> 00:41:54.721
- Is he going up?
- Yeah.

1031
00:41:54.804 --> 00:41:57.390
He's a good guy.

1032
00:41:57.473 --> 00:42:00.268
Our surgeons
will get him through.

1033
00:42:00.309 --> 00:42:04.147
[indistinct chatter. laughter]

1034
00:42:04.230 --> 00:42:06.941
I like her.

1035
00:42:06.983 --> 00:42:08.651
- More than me?

1036
00:42:08.735 --> 00:42:11.112
- Only time will tell.

1037
00:42:11.195 --> 00:42:12.989
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

1038
00:42:13.072 --> 00:42:15.616
She has good command
of staff and procedures.

1039
00:42:15.700 --> 00:42:18.911
I think you're leaving your day
shift in very capable hands.

1040
00:42:18.995 --> 00:42:20.413
- I hope so.

1041
00:42:20.496 --> 00:42:22.373
- All right.
I'm out of here. man.

1042
00:42:22.457 --> 00:42:25.460
I got to be back
in a few hours for my shift.

1043
00:42:25.543 --> 00:42:27.295
- Well. hey.
if I don't see you...

1044
00:42:27.378 --> 00:42:30.048
- You're really doing
this still?

1045
00:42:30.131 --> 00:42:32.091
I don't think I can remember
the last time

1046
00:42:32.175 --> 00:42:33.634
you took three days off
in a row.

1047
00:42:33.718 --> 00:42:36.429
- I've taken a vacation before.

1048
00:42:36.512 --> 00:42:38.389
- Name the last one.

1049
00:42:38.473 --> 00:42:40.975
- [inhales deeply]

1050
00:42:41.059 --> 00:42:43.394
Point taken.

1051
00:42:43.478 --> 00:42:46.773
- It's gonna be a lot of time
to self-reflect.

1052
00:42:49.192 --> 00:42:51.402
You sure you can handle that?

1053
00:42:53.696 --> 00:42:55.448
Okay.

1054
00:42:55.531 --> 00:42:57.617
You just make sure
you come back.

1055
00:42:57.700 --> 00:43:00.411
And if it gets dark.
you call me.

1056
00:43:02.038 --> 00:43:03.790
You listening?

1057
00:43:08.252 --> 00:43:10.505
- So the ankle's negative
for fracture.

1058
00:43:10.546 --> 00:43:12.632
- Wait. go back to the ankle.

1059
00:43:12.715 --> 00:43:14.175
- You see the normal mortise?

1060
00:43:14.258 --> 00:43:17.345
- Yeah. but the tibiofibular
clear space looks enlarged.

1061
00:43:17.386 --> 00:43:20.515
and the tibiofibular overlap
seems reduced.

1062
00:43:20.556 --> 00:43:23.851
- Maybe a little.

1063
00:43:23.935 --> 00:43:26.938
- 8 millimeters. 3 millimeters.

1064
00:43:27.021 --> 00:43:29.357
Seems like a tear
in the syndesmotic ligaments.

1065
00:43:29.440 --> 00:43:31.526
Doesn't that need
surgical fixation?

1066
00:43:31.567 --> 00:43:34.445
- They do.
I can request an MRI.

1067
00:43:34.529 --> 00:43:37.657
Um. have you done
a radiology clerkship before?

1068
00:43:37.740 --> 00:43:40.660
- No. I'm just that good.

1069
00:43:42.411 --> 00:43:46.040
- [chuckles]
- I'm good at things. too.

1070
00:43:46.124 --> 00:43:47.667
[chuckles]

1071
00:43:56.134 --> 00:44:01.055
- Really great work
earlier today. Doctor.

1072
00:44:01.139 --> 00:44:03.724
- Huh.

1073
00:44:03.808 --> 00:44:05.059
Ow. wow.

1074
00:44:05.143 --> 00:44:07.520
You can just call me Whitaker.
- Not a chance.

1075
00:44:07.603 --> 00:44:08.771
You earned that.

1076
00:44:08.855 --> 00:44:10.231
I'm proud of you.

1077
00:44:10.273 --> 00:44:11.899
We all are.

1078
00:44:11.983 --> 00:44:13.192
- Thank you.

1079
00:44:13.234 --> 00:44:15.611
- Busy day.
- Oh. yeah.

1080
00:44:15.695 --> 00:44:18.406
- So you're
a very empathetic soul.

1081
00:44:18.489 --> 00:44:20.741
- Yeah. I'd like to think--
- I'm not finished yet.

1082
00:44:20.783 --> 00:44:23.077
And you want to be there
for all your patients.

1083
00:44:23.161 --> 00:44:24.745
- Don't you?
- Shh.

1084
00:44:24.829 --> 00:44:26.038
- Sorry.

1085
00:44:26.122 --> 00:44:28.332
- So this relationship
that you're having

1086
00:44:28.416 --> 00:44:30.835
with this woman. um.
the widow of the burn victim

1087
00:44:30.918 --> 00:44:32.670
who died last year.
- Amy.

1088
00:44:32.753 --> 00:44:34.088
Santos tell you?

1089
00:44:34.130 --> 00:44:36.507
- I understand
you're helping her out.

1090
00:44:36.591 --> 00:44:38.342
- Yeah. on the farm.

1091
00:44:38.426 --> 00:44:41.262
I grew up on one. and Amy's--

1092
00:44:41.304 --> 00:44:43.848
Mrs. Miller is getting
pressure to sell.

1093
00:44:43.931 --> 00:44:46.017
so I'm just helping out.

1094
00:44:46.100 --> 00:44:48.102
- What about her friends
and family?

1095
00:44:48.144 --> 00:44:49.896
- Yeah. they're around.

1096
00:44:49.979 --> 00:44:51.397
- Supporting her?

1097
00:44:51.480 --> 00:44:52.982
- Yeah. I think they try to.

1098
00:44:53.065 --> 00:44:56.402
but. mostly.
she's just leaning on...

1099
00:44:56.485 --> 00:44:57.904
me.

1100
00:45:00.823 --> 00:45:02.742
- I'm sure
she's really grateful

1101
00:45:02.825 --> 00:45:04.160
for everything that you do.

1102
00:45:04.243 --> 00:45:07.121
but it's important
to have boundaries.

1103
00:45:07.205 --> 00:45:08.539
- Yeah.

1104
00:45:11.709 --> 00:45:14.795
- Hey. you want to do me
a favor?

1105
00:45:14.837 --> 00:45:16.130
- Yeah?

1106
00:45:16.172 --> 00:45:18.966
- You want to house-sit for me
while I'm gone?

1107
00:45:19.008 --> 00:45:20.968
You'd actually be
helping me out.

1108
00:45:21.010 --> 00:45:24.263
and you could save
some money on rent.

1109
00:45:24.347 --> 00:45:25.806
- Are you being serious?

1110
00:45:25.848 --> 00:45:28.809
- No smoking. no parties.
no pets. no babies.

1111
00:45:28.893 --> 00:45:30.603
yours or anybody else's.

1112
00:45:30.686 --> 00:45:33.314
- I don't have a baby.
- No. but she does.

1113
00:45:33.356 --> 00:45:36.442
I was going to ask Abbot. but
he does nude yoga at sunrise.

1114
00:45:36.484 --> 00:45:38.611
and I don't think some
of my elderly neighbors

1115
00:45:38.694 --> 00:45:40.905
would survive seeing that.
- [chuckles]

1116
00:45:40.988 --> 00:45:43.991
Yeah.
Yeah. t-that would be amazing--

1117
00:45:44.033 --> 00:45:47.411
the house-sitting.
not seeing Abbot's naked yoga.

1118
00:45:47.495 --> 00:45:50.164
- If I don't come back. you got
a swinging bachelor pad.

1119
00:45:50.206 --> 00:45:51.624
- Okay.

1120
00:45:53.000 --> 00:45:54.585
- Come find me
before you leave.

1121
00:45:54.669 --> 00:45:56.963
I'll give you my keys
and the security code.

1122
00:45:57.004 --> 00:45:58.172
- Okay.

1123
00:45:58.256 --> 00:46:01.509
- Who's the joker
that did this?

1124
00:46:01.550 --> 00:46:03.552
- Oh.

1125
00:46:03.636 --> 00:46:05.137
- We need some help out there.

1126
00:46:05.221 --> 00:46:07.348
- You two. make sure
to double-check your work.

1127
00:46:07.390 --> 00:46:08.891
Triage could use an extra hand.

1128
00:46:08.975 --> 00:46:11.018
Princess. finish up here.
then head that way.

1129
00:46:11.060 --> 00:46:13.312
- Three for CT now.
Should I run it over?

1130
00:46:13.396 --> 00:46:15.022
- No.
Keep taking off orders.

1131
00:46:15.064 --> 00:46:17.066
- CT's gonna get backed up
if we wait on these.

1132
00:46:17.149 --> 00:46:19.193
- I know. but I can't waste
a runner on that right now.

1133
00:46:19.277 --> 00:46:21.237
- Where'd you find
a carrier sheet?

1134
00:46:21.320 --> 00:46:24.073
- Exactly where I filed it away
ten years ago.

1135
00:46:24.156 --> 00:46:26.158
- I thought that thing
didn't work.

1136
00:46:26.242 --> 00:46:28.035
- Can't receive.
but it can send.

1137
00:46:28.119 --> 00:46:30.913
[telephone ringing]

1138
00:46:35.209 --> 00:46:38.462
- Stay hydrated. preferably
with electrolyte-rich drinks

1139
00:46:38.546 --> 00:46:40.715
like coconut water.
- I'm not a fan of coconuts.

1140
00:46:40.798 --> 00:46:42.383
- Okay. Gatorade's
also an option.

1141
00:46:42.425 --> 00:46:44.677
Just avoid alcohol and
caffeine. and I suggest wearing

1142
00:46:44.760 --> 00:46:46.387
light. breathable clothing.
- Boring.

1143
00:46:46.429 --> 00:46:48.306
- Come back
if your symptoms worsen.

1144
00:46:48.389 --> 00:46:50.057
if you develop
a headache or confusion.

1145
00:46:50.141 --> 00:46:51.392
- Okay.

1146
00:46:51.434 --> 00:46:54.353
Mm.
You sure about that?

1147
00:46:54.437 --> 00:46:56.355
[indistinct chatter]

1148
00:46:56.439 --> 00:46:59.400
- Hey. could you turn that up?
- [gasps]

1149
00:46:59.483 --> 00:47:02.737
- Have responded to a deadly
waterslide collapse

1150
00:47:02.820 --> 00:47:04.238
at a local water park.

1151
00:47:04.322 --> 00:47:06.407
Now. we're told there's
at least one fatality.

1152
00:47:06.490 --> 00:47:07.742
with multiple injuries.

1153
00:47:07.825 --> 00:47:10.870
- Oh. shit.
And they're all coming to us.

1154
00:47:10.953 --> 00:47:13.873
- Currently being airlifted
to the hospital by heli--

1154
00:47:14.305 --> 00:48:14.828
